00:43:27,808 --> 00:43:28,832
But I got my revenge.

1390
00:43:29,536 --> 00:43:31,104
I'm so happy inside.

1391
00:43:31,584 --> 00:43:32,928
Being the Invisible Hand is great.

1392
00:43:34,944 --> 00:43:35,744
You got revenge.

1393
00:43:35,744 --> 00:43:37,088
(What kind of revenge is that?)
Who hit you just now?

1394
00:43:37,472 --> 00:43:38,080
(Blurting out)
Li Naiwen.

1395
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:38,680
What?

1396
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:40,416
When did I hit you?

1397
00:43:41,728 --> 00:43:43,040
He's getting revenge for an old grudge.

1398
00:43:43,264 --> 00:43:44,352
Revenge from last season?

1399
00:43:44,352 --> 00:43:45,152
Blood and tears.

1400
00:43:45,152 --> 00:43:46,336
It's a history of blood and tears.

1401
00:43:46,336 --> 00:43:47,520
Everyone, put your blindfolds on.

1402
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:50,272
There's still one more person.

1403
00:43:50,272 --> 00:43:51,424
Why are you putting it on? Get out.

1404
00:43:55,904 --> 00:43:57,160
Can I be a substitute hitter?

1405
00:43:57,160 --> 00:43:57,792
(Immediately rejected)
No.

1406
00:43:57,792 --> 00:43:58,272
Substitute hitter?

1407
00:43:58,272 --> 00:43:59,680
That job doesn't exist, right?

1408
00:43:59,872 --> 00:44:00,256
(Substitute hitter career ends with regret)
Fine.

1409
00:44:00,992 --> 00:44:02,048
You can be a substitute for getting hit.

1410
00:44:03,648 --> 00:44:04,672
So there's just one left.

1411
00:44:05,408 --> 00:44:06,720
(Watch my performance)

1412
00:44:07,392 --> 00:44:09,088
Their game quotient is extremely high.

1413
00:44:09,952 --> 00:44:12,480
Three, two, one, go.

1414
00:44:14,752 --> 00:44:15,360
Has it started?

1415
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:17,312
- It's started.
- Guo Jingfei.

1416
00:44:18,208 --> 00:44:19,168
Come on, one, two, three.

1417
00:44:20,928 --> 00:44:21,440
One, two.

1418
00:44:21,568 --> 00:44:21,920
Who is it?

1419
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:22,528
I'm here.

1420
00:44:23,917 --> 00:44:24,608
(Appreciative look)

1421
00:44:26,560 --> 00:44:27,648
(Off-field distraction)
Wang Yuwen.

1422
00:44:28,096 --> 00:44:28,640
Wang Yuwen.

1423
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:29,952
What? I'm here.

1424
00:44:30,304 --> 00:44:31,040
Wang Yuwen.

1425
00:44:33,293 --> 00:44:34,176
(Jun's scapegoat: Wang Yuwen)

1426
00:44:34,176 --> 00:44:36,160
I'm here.

1427
00:44:36,160 --> 00:44:37,792
(Scapegoat passing by)
I'm talking.

1428
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:39,264
Wang Yuwen.

1429
00:44:39,904 --> 00:44:40,864
It's Wang Yuwen.

1430
00:44:40,864 --> 00:44:41,568
(Successfully framed)
It's not me.

1431
00:44:41,568 --> 00:44:42,240
Wang Yuwen.

1432
00:44:42,464 --> 00:44:43,488
Wang Yuwen, keep talking.

1433
00:44:43,488 --> 00:44:44,280
Wang Yuwen, keep talking.

1434
00:44:44,280 --> 00:44:44,896
Talk.

1435
00:44:44,896 --> 00:44:45,792
It's not me.

1436
00:44:46,528 --> 00:44:48,224
How could it be me?

1437
00:44:51,936 --> 00:44:52,608
Wang Yuwen?

1438
00:44:52,608 --> 00:44:53,400
(Believed it was true)

1439
00:44:53,632 --> 00:44:54,496
It's Wang Yuwen.

1440
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:55,968
Wang Yuwen.

1441
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:57,440
(Poke poke poke)

1442
00:44:57,952 --> 00:44:58,680
Wang Yuwen.

1443
00:44:58,848 --> 00:45:00,680
That hit just now was you, right?

1444
00:45:00,928 --> 00:45:02,304
What did I do?

1445
00:45:02,304 --> 00:45:03,488
It's her.

1446
00:45:03,488 --> 00:45:04,224
Speak, Wang Yuwen.

1447
00:45:04,608 --> 00:45:05,376
Wang Yuwen, speak.

1448
00:45:05,792 --> 00:45:06,592
Speak, Wang Yuwen.

1449
00:45:07,264 --> 00:45:08,992
(Seems not resisting
but actually frustrated)

1450
00:45:08,992 --> 00:45:09,824
Wang Yuwen, speak.

1451
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:10,784
Wang Yuwen, speak.

1452
00:45:10,784 --> 00:45:11,968
(Weak counterattack)
Foolish.

1453
00:45:12,224 --> 00:45:13,184
Wang Yuwen.

1454
00:45:13,632 --> 00:45:14,640
It's Wang Yuwen.

1455
00:45:14,848 --> 00:45:15,808
Wang Yuwen, talk.

1456
00:45:16,352 --> 00:45:17,152
Where's Wang Yuwen?

1457
00:45:17,152 --> 00:45:18,080
Wang Yuwen, talk.

1458
00:45:18,272 --> 00:45:19,232
She's not even talking anymore.

1459
00:45:19,616 --> 00:45:20,448
(I feel for you, Yuwen)
Wang Yuwen, talk.

1460
00:45:21,184 --> 00:45:22,160
I am talking.

1461
00:45:22,368 --> 00:45:23,648
I am talking.

1462
00:45:23,712 --> 00:45:25,152
I talked.

1463
00:45:25,152 --> 00:45:25,984
On the left.

1464
00:45:26,336 --> 00:45:27,200
Wang Yuwen.

1465
00:45:27,200 --> 00:45:28,224
It's Wang Yuwen.

1466
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,528
Hey, it's not Wang Yuwen.

1467
00:45:31,456 --> 00:45:32,768
(Overdid it)

1468
00:45:34,016 --> 00:45:35,136
It's not me, how could it be me?

1469
00:45:35,136 --> 00:45:36,512
Three, two, one.

1470
00:45:37,632 --> 00:45:38,336
Please open your eyes.

1471
00:45:40,224 --> 00:45:40,832
You went back again.

1472
00:45:40,832 --> 00:45:41,792
(What are the odds?)
You're too slow again.

1473
00:45:41,792 --> 00:45:43,008
A bit slow.

1474
00:45:43,008 --> 00:45:44,000
You're a bit slow.

1475
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:46,240
You didn't even have time to
put on the blindfold?

1476
00:45:46,816 --> 00:45:48,064
You put it halfway on and then realized

1477
00:45:48,064 --> 00:45:49,344
we had already taken ours off.

1478
00:45:49,824 --> 00:45:50,960
It's hanging on my ear.

1479
00:45:51,136 --> 00:45:52,736
I couldn't take it off.

1480
00:45:52,736 --> 00:45:53,792
So fast.

1481
00:45:53,792 --> 00:45:55,200
Like a fox that just stole a chicken.

1482
00:45:59,488 --> 00:46:00,160
Your eyes were like this.

1483
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:13,480
Don't.

1484
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:14,016
Don't.

1485
00:46:14,016 --> 00:46:15,008
Don't pout.

1486
00:46:15,744 --> 00:46:16,240
Don't.

1487
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:16,832
Like this.

1488
00:46:18,656 --> 00:46:19,936
(Hold it in)

1489
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:22,624
You really can't hold it in anymore.

1490
00:46:23,168 --> 00:46:24,360
Are you accusing me?

1491
00:46:24,544 --> 00:46:25,568
You'll know how foolish that is

1492
00:46:25,568 --> 00:46:27,840
when the time comes.

1493
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:29,440
Don't stutter.

1494
00:46:29,888 --> 00:46:31,232
Stupid.

1495
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:34,464
Look at her.

1496
00:46:35,168 --> 00:46:36,240
No, let her speak.

1497
00:46:36,352 --> 00:46:37,400
Let her explain first.

1498
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:38,912
Let her speak first.

1499
00:46:39,232 --> 00:46:41,152
What's your psychological motive?

1500
00:46:41,504 --> 00:46:42,656
Where did it start?

1501
00:46:42,656 --> 00:46:44,240
Why did you go there?

1502
00:46:44,416 --> 00:46:46,080
My starting point was at that pillar.

1503
00:46:46,944 --> 00:46:48,064
Your starting point was here.

1504
00:46:48,064 --> 00:46:48,800
But we were all moving.

1505
00:46:48,800 --> 00:46:50,464
So how did you end up still here?

1506
00:46:50,760 --> 00:46:53,120
Because holding this,
I could feel my way along the edge.

1507
00:46:53,728 --> 00:46:55,104
(The Invisible Hand is amused)
Feel you way along the edge again?

1508
00:46:56,768 --> 00:46:58,560
You felt your way along people,
didn't you?

1509
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:01,240
Let me replay my actions.

1510
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:03,160
I started here.

1511
00:47:03,328 --> 00:47:04,880
Then I was feeling my way here.

1512
00:47:05,024 --> 00:47:07,000
When you met the first person,
you poked him.

1513
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:09,600
I heard someone over there
telling me to speak.

1514
00:47:09,792 --> 00:47:11,904
So I followed the sound
and walked this way.

1515
00:47:11,904 --> 00:47:14,360
Then I ended up next to Yuning.

1516
00:47:14,592 --> 00:47:16,040
(Continuing to pile on)
How did you know it was Yuning?

1517
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:17,600
I... There was a voice.

1518
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:18,432
Right, that makes sense.

1519
00:47:18,784 --> 00:47:19,168
Right?

1520
00:47:19,168 --> 00:47:20,320
Then nothing was happening.

1521
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:21,400
So I walked back.

1522
00:47:22,144 --> 00:47:22,976
Your sense of direction!

1523
00:47:24,192 --> 00:47:24,896
Then you walked over here...

1524
00:47:24,896 --> 00:47:26,200
Great sense of direction.

1525
00:47:26,368 --> 00:47:28,384
You knew you were going back?

1526
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:30,040
You were here.

1527
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:31,200
You just came straight back.

1528
00:47:31,200 --> 00:47:32,032
You know what?

1529
00:47:32,032 --> 00:47:32,864
After we took off our blindfolds,

1530
00:47:32,864 --> 00:47:33,728
you still stepped this way.

1531
00:47:33,728 --> 00:47:34,432
Returned to the starting point.

1532
00:47:35,744 --> 00:47:36,768
Impressive.

1533
00:47:38,112 --> 00:47:39,424
Then I was holding on to this.

1534
00:47:39,424 --> 00:47:40,128
And then,

1535
00:47:40,128 --> 00:47:41,472
you kept calling "Wang Yuwen"
from behind.

1536
00:47:41,472 --> 00:47:42,600
I said you were stupid.

1537
00:47:42,784 --> 00:47:44,400
I was just about to explain something,

1538
00:47:44,576 --> 00:47:45,728
when they said "Open your eyes."

1539
00:47:45,824 --> 00:47:47,360
Then I walked back again.

1540
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:48,360
After I opened my eyes,

1541
00:47:48,544 --> 00:47:50,112
you saw me here.

1542
00:47:50,656 --> 00:47:52,160
Then you were about
to put on the blindfold,

1543
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:53,640
but it got stuck halfway.

1544
00:47:53,824 --> 00:47:54,656
Your route

1545
00:47:54,656 --> 00:47:56,680
looks so much
like a route without a blindfold.

1546
00:47:57,792 --> 00:47:59,240
(So wronged)

1547
00:47:59,392 --> 00:48:01,504
I'm telling you the truth.

1548
00:48:01,504 --> 00:48:02,368
(Only those who wronged you)

1549
00:48:02,368 --> 00:48:03,552
(know how wronged you are)

1550
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:05,760
There are only two possibilities.

1551
00:48:05,760 --> 00:48:07,648
Either you're really evil

1552
00:48:07,648 --> 00:48:08,096
and came to hit us.

1553
00:48:08,096 --> 00:48:08,672
Or you're the type

1554
00:48:08,672 --> 00:48:09,632
who's quite idle

1555
00:48:09,632 --> 00:48:10,368
but likes to stir things up.

1556
00:48:11,264 --> 00:48:12,224
Where were you?

1557
00:48:13,376 --> 00:48:14,680
Where were you hit?

1558
00:48:14,848 --> 00:48:16,224
I wasn't hit in the last round.

1559
00:48:16,544 --> 00:48:17,376
You weren't hit?

1560
00:48:20,332 --> 00:48:21,376
(I can't explain it anymore)

1561
00:48:23,040 --> 00:48:25,088
I really wasn't hit last round.

1562
00:48:25,088 --> 00:48:25,792
I really...

1563
00:48:27,616 --> 00:48:28,352
There's no way to explain.

1564
00:48:29,792 --> 00:48:30,880
She's caught in her own defense.

1565
00:48:31,456 --> 00:48:32,544
Just assume we wronged you.

1566
00:48:32,544 --> 00:48:33,440
Forgive us, okay?

1567
00:48:33,680 --> 00:48:34,272
Right.

1568
00:48:34,272 --> 00:48:35,200
We wronged...

1569
00:48:35,200 --> 00:48:36,400
Just assume we wronged you.

1570
00:48:36,608 --> 00:48:37,568
I believe it's not you.

1571
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:40,192
(Even an enemy would feel sorry for me)

1572
00:48:43,488 --> 00:48:44,864
(Voting time)
Three, two, one, please vote.

1573
00:48:44,864 --> 00:48:45,792
(Wang Yuwen is eliminated)

1574
00:48:45,792 --> 00:48:46,240
Alright.

1575
00:48:46,464 --> 00:48:47,648
Yuwen's identity is...

1576
00:48:48,608 --> 00:48:49,088
Good Person.

1577
00:48:56,704 --> 00:48:59,008
Great. Congratulations.

1578
00:48:59,008 --> 00:49:01,152
What I just said was true.

1579
00:49:01,152 --> 00:49:01,840
I really...

1580
00:49:01,984 --> 00:49:02,944
You looked really anxious.

1581
00:49:02,944 --> 00:49:03,936
I really sympathize.

1582
00:49:04,064 --> 00:49:05,152
I really sympathize.

1583
00:49:06,016 --> 00:49:06,816
"Invisible Hand" wins.

1584
00:49:06,816 --> 00:49:08,416
You can continue guessing who it is.

1585
00:49:09,152 --> 00:49:11,328
(Invisible Hand hid successfully)

1586
00:49:11,328 --> 00:49:12,480
(Stay locked on)

1587
00:49:12,672 --> 00:49:13,728
Guo Jingfei.

1588
00:49:16,128 --> 00:49:17,632
No, we were standing close together.

1589
00:49:17,632 --> 00:49:18,848
We were standing close the whole time.

1590
00:49:19,456 --> 00:49:20,480
I kept calling Jingfei.

1591
00:49:20,480 --> 00:49:21,840
But he never replied to me.

1592
00:49:22,016 --> 00:49:23,008
I was nervous.

1593
00:49:23,008 --> 00:49:24,096
I-I-I didn't...

1594
00:49:24,480 --> 00:49:25,120
You were nervous,

1595
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:25,568
so you didn't speak?

1596
00:49:25,568 --> 00:49:26,304
Why were you nervous?

1597
00:49:26,304 --> 00:49:27,008
Why were you nervous?

1598
00:49:27,008 --> 00:49:27,808
(Good Person is proving themselves again)
It wasn't true.

1599
00:49:27,808 --> 00:49:28,544
I wasn't...

1600
00:49:29,472 --> 00:49:29,888
Here's the thing.

1601
00:49:29,888 --> 00:49:31,104
Why were you nervous?

1602
00:49:33,696 --> 00:49:34,976
You hit someone.
Of course you were nervous.

1603
00:49:34,976 --> 00:49:36,960
You guys are like hungry wolves.

1604
00:49:36,960 --> 00:49:37,600
You know?

1605
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:39,320
(Listening to your defense)
You jump at any meat you see.

1606
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:40,256
Listen to me.

1607
00:49:40,256 --> 00:49:40,880
Then it's him.

1608
00:49:40,880 --> 00:49:41,536
You go ahead.

1609
00:49:41,536 --> 00:49:41,952
I vote him out.

1610
00:49:42,624 --> 00:49:43,072
Wait.

1611
00:49:43,456 --> 00:49:45,040
When I was in college...

1612
00:49:45,216 --> 00:49:46,840
When I was in college...

1613
00:49:47,008 --> 00:49:48,288
When I was in college...

1614
00:49:51,808 --> 00:49:53,440
The day when I was born...

1615
00:49:53,632 --> 00:49:55,008
A childhood trauma now?

1616
00:49:55,776 --> 00:49:57,664
How did it become such a long story?

1617
00:49:58,272 --> 00:49:59,936
You didn't know how to explain it,

1618
00:49:59,936 --> 00:50:00,928
so you started from further back.

1619
00:50:01,312 --> 00:50:03,072
Let him finish.

1620
00:50:04,064 --> 00:50:04,352
Well,

1621
00:50:04,352 --> 00:50:05,840
I took this lesson
in performance practice.

1622
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:06,200
Right.

1623
00:50:06,304 --> 00:50:06,960
When our eyes were closed,

1624
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:08,992
I was the only one
in my class who didn't move.

1625
00:50:08,992 --> 00:50:10,208
Everyone else dared to move forward.

1626
00:50:10,208 --> 00:50:11,104
Then why were you nervous?

1627
00:50:11,104 --> 00:50:12,288
I was afraid of the dark.

1628
00:50:12,288 --> 00:50:13,024
I was afraid of bumping.

1629
00:50:14,816 --> 00:50:15,680
Look at my age.

1630
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:16,864
You've all felt my heartbeat.

1631
00:50:16,864 --> 00:50:18,080
Was I out of breath after playing?

1632
00:50:18,432 --> 00:50:19,872
That shows you usually exercise.

1633
00:50:22,880 --> 00:50:23,904
Given what you said,

1634
00:50:24,288 --> 00:50:24,864
it's me.

1635
00:50:24,864 --> 00:50:25,376
(I admit it)

1636
00:50:28,032 --> 00:50:28,960
So you two were

1637
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:30,496
connected the whole time.

1638
00:50:30,496 --> 00:50:30,880
Right?

1639
00:50:31,424 --> 00:50:31,680
Yes.

1640
00:50:31,680 --> 00:50:32,800
We were connected.

1641
00:50:32,960 --> 00:50:34,464
So do you two suspect each other?

1642
00:50:34,464 --> 00:50:35,072
No.

1643
00:50:35,072 --> 00:50:35,640
No?

1644
00:50:35,808 --> 00:50:36,960
I don't suspect myself either.

1645
00:50:36,960 --> 00:50:37,920
I don't suspect Nai either.

1646
00:50:38,048 --> 00:50:38,912
But I suspect you.

1647
00:50:40,672 --> 00:50:41,952
(Continuing to stir things up)
You've been talking a lot this round.

1648
00:50:41,952 --> 00:50:43,160
Didn't I talk a lot last round?

1649
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:44,600
You didn't talk much last round.

1650
00:50:44,768 --> 00:50:45,344
Zhou Ye,

1651
00:50:45,344 --> 00:50:45,920
it's you.

1652
00:50:46,240 --> 00:50:46,656
Wait,

1653
00:50:46,656 --> 00:50:47,520
first tell me

1654
00:50:47,520 --> 00:50:48,672
why you screamed in the first round

1655
00:50:48,672 --> 00:50:49,696
as if you were being kidnapped.

1656
00:50:49,696 --> 00:50:50,528
You screamed for so long.

1657
00:50:50,528 --> 00:50:52,000
Did someone keep doing this to you?

1658
00:50:52,544 --> 00:50:54,144
(One hit leads to screaming for long)

1659
00:50:54,208 --> 00:50:55,168
Because I was scared.

1660
00:50:56,192 --> 00:50:56,928
I just poked once.

1661
00:50:56,928 --> 00:50:58,000
Then you kept screaming.

1662
00:50:58,176 --> 00:50:58,840
